=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 13, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104kvw1665702705043.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/kvw1665702705043.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/kvw1665702705043.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"kvw1665702705043\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Referential Integrity Management on ODBC\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"kvw1665702705043__referential_integrity_management_on_odbc_163414\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kvw1665702705043__p_d54893e1_d54894e1_d54895e1\">Referential integrity is handled by Uniface.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"kvw1665702705043__topic_d36277e1_d36278e1_d36279e1_d36280e1_d36281e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d431106e59\">\n                        \n Commit and Rollback\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kvw1665702705043__p_d54899e1_d54900e1_d54901e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">commit</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">rollback</span> statements are supported provided the chosen DBMS supports these statements.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kvw1665702705043__p_d54902e1_d54903e1_d54904e1\">Two-phase commit is not supported.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"kvw1665702705043__topic_d36282e1_d36283e1_d36284e1_d36285e1_d36286e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d431106e77\">\n                        \n Locking\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kvw1665702705043__p_d54908e1_d54909e1_d54910e1\">All Uniface locking types are supported if the DBMS supports them.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kvw1665702705043__p_d54911e1_d54912e1_d54913e1\">The default locking type is optimistic. You can specify the locking type for tables that share the same ODBC Connector (for example OD1) by using the <code class=\"ph codeph\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fug1665702705112.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fug1665702705112.html\" title=\"Set the default locking strategy employed by Uniface.\">default locking</a>\n</code> connector option. However, if the locking type is specified in Uniface Application Model, it overrides any locking type specified using the <code class=\"ph codeph\">default locking</code> option.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"kvw1665702705043__topic_d36287e1_d36288e1_d36289e1_d36290e1_d36291e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d431106e102\">\n                        \n read/lock\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kvw1665702705043__d6538e20\">You can specify paranoid locking by using the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">read</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">/lock</code> ProcScript command in the read trigger of an entity.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"kvw1665702705043__topic_d36292e1_d36293e1_d36294e1_d36295e1_d36296e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d431106e118\">\n                        \n U_VERSION\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kvw1665702705043__p_d54923e1_d54924e1_d54925e1\">The ODBC Connector supports the U_VERSION mechanism to improve locking performance. It is strongly recommended that you use U_VERSION because this significantly reduces the chance of lock conflicts.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529392\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529392\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Referential Integrity Management on ODBC Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 13, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Referential Integrity Management on ODBC Referential integrity is handled by Uniface. Commit and Rollback The commit and rollback statements are supported provided the chosen DBMS supports these statements. Two-phase commit is not supported. Locking All Uniface locking types are supported if the DBMS supports them. The default locking type is optimistic. You can specify the locking type for tables that share the same ODBC Connector (for example OD1) by using the default locking connector option. However, if the locking type is specified in Uniface Application Model, it overrides any locking type specified using the default locking option. read/lock You can specify paranoid locking by using the read /lock ProcScript command in the read trigger of an entity. U_VERSION The ODBC Connector supports the U_VERSION mechanism to improve locking performance. It is strongly recommended that you use U_VERSION because this significantly reduces the chance of lock conflicts. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}